[normal]5[bold].[bold]              [bold]Corporate Governance [bold]and reputation[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]5
[normal].1
[normal]              
[normal] 
[normal]London is one of the world
[normal]’
[normal]s leading financial centres and attracts a wide range of companies to list on its markets.  
[normal]As well as having 
[normal]significant expe
[normal]rtise in mining and extractives, a 
[normal]key strength of the UK and its financial institutions is
[normal] its 
[normal]strong corporate governance framework,
[normal] 
[normal]which is robust by comparison to many countries in which extractives may operate.  A listing on the London Stock Exchange
[normal] is evidence that a company is held to a high standard which promotes confidence when dealing with that company. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.2
[normal]              
[normal]The extractive industry has a unique risk profile as a result of the varied projects that the average extractive 
[normal]company 
[normal]carries out. 
[normal]The
[normal]s
[normal]e projects are 
[normal]often in countries carrying greater risks
[normal] which 
[normal]require permits and licen
[normal]c
[normal]es. 
[normal] Th
[normal]ere are particular r
[normal]isks 
[normal]which 
[normal]extractive companies 
[normal]could be 
[normal]particularly exposed
[normal] to
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]T
[normal]hese 
[normal]might 
[normal]be
[normal] reputational, operational
[normal], environmental
[normal] 
[normal]as well as
[normal] bribery and corruption risk
[normal]s
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal]The UK’s existing regu
[normal]latory regime helps to mitigate
[normal] these risks.
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]Extractive companies 
[normal]have a responsibility to ensure that their corporate governance is compliant with the regulatory regime. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3
[normal]              
[normal]In itself, the number of
[normal] extractives listing in the UK should not pose any concerns if they are compliant with the regulatory regime.   However, 
[normal]there are a num
[normal]ber of events that would raise
[normal] concern
[normal]s
[normal] that the regulatory regime is being improperly applied.  This includes, but is n
[normal]ot limited to:
[normal]i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a 
[normal]significant 
[normal]number of companies displaying corporate governance failures;
[normal]ii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]inadequate
[normal] 
[normal]monitoring or 
[normal]enforcement of failures 
[normal]of cor
[normal]porate governance on an industrial
[normal] scale
[normal];
[normal]iii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]corporate governance failures affecting the market value of extracti
[normal]ves across the industry as a whole and
[normal];
[normal]iv)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]a significant
[normal] number of companies listing in London
[normal] 
[normal]that pose a significantly higher risk
[normal] profile 
[normal]than the average FTSE listing.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.4
[normal]              
[normal]Without mitigating these risks, 
[normal]investors 
[normal]could 
[normal]question the 
[normal]effectiveness of the 
[normal]UK
[normal] regulatory framework as whole
[normal], with inherent reputational risks to the UK and its financial institutions. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.5
[normal]              
[normal]At present, there are concerns that the interests of minority shareholders are under-represented in companies where ther
[normal]e are powerful majority shareholders and in companies which are traded publicly but have a relatively small proportion of shares in public circulation. In both these situation
[normal]s there is a concern about
[normal] the increased concentrations of shareholder power in t
[normal]he hands of the few
[normal]. This means
[normal] it is less likely that minority shareholders will be able to make their views known and hold directors to account in the event of corporate governance failures. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5
[normal].
[normal]6
[normal]              
[normal]These issues have been considered by the UK Listing Autho
[normal]rity.  The FCA consulted last October
[normal] on proposals to enhance the effectiveness of the Listing Regime overall and in particular to provide greater protection to shareholders in situations where there is a controlling shareholder.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] FCA intend
[normal]s 
[normal]to provide f
[normal]eedback on this consultation in October. 
