[normal]9[bold].[bold]              [bold]Role of regulation [bold]&#xa0;
[normal]9
[normal].1
[normal]              
[normal]London is one of the world’s leading financial centres and attracts a wide range of companies to list on its markets.  One reason for this is 
[normal]our
[normal] legal and regulatory framework.  
[normal]While m
[normal]any companies list in their geographic home, other companies will have a choice of location and as a result the UK is in competition with other markets, in particular the US.  
[normal]A
[normal]ny decision to change the regulatory s
[normal]ystem would need to be taken in this context and maintain the competitiveness of the UK market for issuers whilst providing an appropriate degree of protection for investors. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9
[normal].2
[normal]              
[normal]Notwithstanding the need to maintain a competitive environment, the UK is r
[normal]egarded as a centre of excellence for best practice and corporate governance
[normal].  A high value is 
[normal]place
[normal]d
[normal] on the trust and transparency of 
[normal]the UK’s 
[normal]corporate governance framework.  
[normal]T
[normal]o enhance this further, 
[normal]BIS
[normal] recently published 
[normal]a
[normal] discussion paper on Transpare
[normal]ncy &amp; Trust
[normal].
[normal]  
[normal]It
[normal] introduces proposals to improve the transparency of corporate ownership structures in the UK and to increase trust in companies and those who run them by ensuring that we have adequate and robust sanctions in place when the rules are brok
[normal]en.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]9
[normal].3
[normal]              
[normal]The Financial Conduct Authority, as the independent regulator for the UK’s listing regime, consulted last October on proposals to enhance the effectiveness of the Listing Regime overall and in particular to provide greater protection to 
[normal]investors
[normal] 
[normal]in situations where there is a controlling shareholder.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] 
[normal]The 
[normal]FCA is
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]intending to provide feedback on this consultation in early October. 
